19:09.122 --> 19:10.330
- That's great.
- Yeah.

19:10.380 --> 19:13.907
- Uh, so are these kids...
- They have autism.

19:13.995 --> 19:15.502
And music helps them?

19:15.508 --> 19:17.362
Well, music is a non-verbal language.

19:17.398 --> 19:18.913
So, the kids make music

19:18.927 --> 19:21.295
and I can connect with them
by answering back musically.

19:21.301 --> 19:23.134
- That's really cool.
- Yeah.

19:23.537 --> 19:25.470
Is there anything I can do to help?

19:25.506 --> 19:28.020
Um, it would be a huge help if you can

19:28.038 --> 19:30.509
- put away any loose instruments.
- Sure.

19:48.176 --> 19:51.063
This... is... my... pat-tern.

19:51.144 --> 19:54.092
Play... it... back... to... me.

19:56.101 --> 19:57.499
Go.

19:57.543 --> 19:59.076
No, it's okay. You can do it.

19:59.099 --> 20:00.897
You can do it. Here you go.

20:00.928 --> 20:02.766
Hey, hey, hey. Oli,
it's okay. It's okay.

20:02.779 --> 20:05.485
Do you want some time?
Do you want your fidget?

20:05.605 --> 20:07.315
Yeah, there you go.

20:07.630 --> 20:09.212
Good job, Oli.

20:09.792 --> 20:11.783
You don't touch a child with autism.

20:11.806 --> 20:13.186
- I didn't know.
- Exactly.

20:13.199 --> 20:14.269
You're here to observe,

20:14.296 --> 20:16.570
- and if you can't do that...
- I'm sorry, I...

20:18.399 --> 20:20.148
