29:37.582 --> 29:38.835
Oh, I know I'm funny.

29:38.880 --> 29:40.962
Oh, you know you're funny?

29:40.998 --> 29:43.969
You're a little punk is
what you are, you little...

29:45.672 --> 29:48.252
- Is this all of it?
- Callie?

29:48.778 --> 29:49.519
Hey.

29:49.542 --> 29:52.077
- Are you behind this boycott at the Open House?
- No.

29:52.104 --> 29:53.353
What boycott?

29:54.086 --> 29:57.912
Some of the seniors are refusing
to put up their senior projects.

29:57.921 --> 30:00.254
And they're pressuring
other students not to attend.

30:00.307 --> 30:02.663
- Why?
- Because they made me take mine down.

30:02.676 --> 30:05.216
So if you had nothing to do
with this, do you know who does?

30:06.475 --> 30:08.338
- No.
- If I find out otherwise...

30:08.349 --> 30:09.692
Don't threaten my daughter.

30:09.812 --> 30:11.456
If she says she's not a
part of this, she's not.

30:11.484 --> 30:14.186
Right. Because this would be the
first time she's ever lied to you.

30:17.129 --> 30:19.225
Look, if the seniors don't show up,

30:19.455 --> 30:24.005
the school, your kids' school
and our jobs are at stake.

30:28.893 --> 30:30.640
- I'm sorry.
- No, no, no.

30:30.668 --> 30:32.101
This is not your fault.

30:32.921 --> 30:34.349
It's my fault. I never
should've asked you

30:34.349 --> 30:36.149
to take your project down to begin with.

30:36.316 --> 30:38.166
I should've fought for you and I'm

30:38.211 --> 30:40.364
actually really proud
that your classmates are.

30:40.392 --> 30:42.006
I don't want to hurt the school.

30:42.361 --> 30:43.979
You know what? That's on Monte.

30:44.204 --> 30:45.758
She could always change her mind.

30:46.675 --> 30:49.003
Actually, I do have an idea.

30:49.601 --> 30:52.010
But I don't think
Monte's going to like it.

30:54.909 --> 30:57.210
- Just have to leave a little early for school.
- Yeah.

30:57.434 --> 31:00.081
Hey, Callie, can I talk
with your mom alone, please?

31:00.158 --> 31:02.230
- Okay.
- Thanks, hon.

31:07.178 --> 31:09.035
Have you... Have you seen this?

31:09.740 --> 31:11.309
What is this? What is Pump?

31:11.318 --> 31:13.675
It's an app for gay men
to hook up with each other.

31:13.795 --> 31:14.928
Who downloaded this?

31:15.048 --> 31:17.630
There's only one gay
man on our family plan.

31:17.827 --> 31:19.144
Boy, you mean?

31:20.602 --> 31:21.616
Where is Jude?

31:21.625 --> 31:24.097
He said he was going
to Taylor's to study.

31:26.808 --> 31:27.809
Hey!

31:28.668 --> 31:31.203
- What's going on?
- I don't know, bud. You tell me.

31:31.225 --> 31:32.974
Did you download this app?

31:35.583 --> 31:36.421
Pump?

31:37.262 --> 31:38.291
What's that?

31:40.121 --> 31:41.532
May I please have your phone, Jude?

31:42.992 --> 31:44.435
Now, Jude.

31:51.059 --> 31:53.123
So you went to meet this man that you

31:53.123 --> 31:55.339
met on an app at his apartment?

31:56.489 --> 31:59.416
Jude, we need to know
everything that happened.

31:59.536 --> 32:01.533
- We're not going to judge.
- Nothing.

32:03.587 --> 32:04.723
He got mad.

32:05.609 --> 32:07.424
I told him I was 18.

32:07.910 --> 32:09.393
And he didn't believe me.

32:09.513 --> 32:11.803
So he told me to get out.

32:13.030 --> 32:15.771
- You're telling us the truth?
- Yes.

32:15.891 --> 32:18.486
- I promise.
- Honey, why were you crying?

32:19.582 --> 32:20.949
Because I was scared.

32:22.387 --> 32:23.961
Being in his apartment,

32:24.081 --> 32:26.716
he thought I was trying
to get him arrested.

32:27.170 --> 32:31.098
Then why did you go there
in the first place, bud?

32:31.376 --> 32:33.062
'Cause I didn't know what to do.

32:35.178 --> 32:36.540
For sex.

32:37.673 --> 32:39.201
They don't talk about it in Health.

32:39.321 --> 32:40.990
And I don't have anyone to ask.

32:41.178 --> 32:44.783
Jude, you are 14. You don't
need to know what to do.

32:44.814 --> 32:47.485
- You're too young to be having sex.
- Okay,

32:47.605 --> 32:48.761
it's true, but...

32:48.784 --> 32:53.593
we teach straight kids what to do
at 14, you know, just in case...

32:54.393 --> 32:56.164
and we advise them to wait,

32:56.635 --> 32:59.493
but they have questions
and we give them answers.

32:59.696 --> 33:02.203
Where do LGBT kids go for answers?

33:02.257 --> 33:03.462
Not to an app,

33:03.669 --> 33:07.174
where you could meet
strangers who could hurt you.

33:08.185 --> 33:11.789
Do you have any idea how much danger
you put yourself in there, Jude?

33:14.612 --> 33:16.729
What if he raped you, buddy?

33:16.756 --> 33:18.949
There are so many what-ifs.

33:18.998 --> 33:20.482
Each worse than the other.

33:20.505 --> 33:23.835
I know that you have
better judgment than this.

33:23.853 --> 33:26.024
Honey, we want you, when you're ready,

33:26.428 --> 33:27.965
and hopefully, when you're older,

33:28.576 --> 33:30.823
to have positive sexual experiences,

33:31.053 --> 33:33.418
not ones that could scar you for life.

33:36.573 --> 33:38.114
Hey, listen.

33:39.278 --> 33:42.092
Enough of the lecture. Just please...

33:42.380 --> 33:45.611
promise us you'll never do
anything like this ever again.

33:47.444 --> 33:49.040
- I promise.
- Okay.

34:03.981 --> 34:06.948
_

34:08.335 --> 34:09.549
What's this?

34:10.741 --> 34:12.867
Well, if we can't teach
our kids on campus,

34:12.889 --> 34:15.284
I'm gonna make sure they
get informed off campus.

34:15.304 --> 34:16.400
Fair enough.

34:17.581 --> 34:19.172
So, good news.

34:19.877 --> 34:22.273
The seniors backed down.
They're showing their projects.

34:22.344 --> 34:24.920
So, all's well that ends well.

34:25.951 --> 34:27.456
Can I talk to you?

34:32.154 --> 34:34.188
Oh, good. Good job, McKenna.

34:39.779 --> 34:43.797
Uh, so, listen. I'm sorry, I...

34:44.216 --> 34:46.264
I overstepped last time, and...

34:46.319 --> 34:49.254
I'm here to observe if you'll have me.

34:49.649 --> 34:53.083
And I promise I'll hang back,
you won't even know I'm here.

34:53.909 --> 34:55.286
Sounds good.

35:10.794 --> 35:12.776
How do you think this
is going to go down?

35:13.347 --> 35:14.650
I'm not sure.

35:18.196 --> 35:19.391
Uh-oh.

35:24.525 --> 35:26.159
What the hell is this?

35:26.194 --> 35:28.858
Well, you didn't want Callie
to show her project on campus,

35:28.899 --> 35:30.853
this is how she got the
seniors to back down.

35:31.566 --> 35:33.325
Showing it off campus.

35:34.534 --> 35:35.919
All's well that ends well, right?

35:44.596 --> 35:47.239
So, clearly I'm a disaster,

35:47.243 --> 35:50.565
and the universe is telling
me that this is not my thing.

35:50.745 --> 35:52.237
Come on.

35:54.269 --> 35:55.806
How did Oli do today?

35:55.820 --> 35:58.006
He had a really big breakthrough.

35:58.741 --> 35:59.964
He laughed.

36:01.038 --> 36:02.341
He did?

36:02.880 --> 36:04.502
And you can thank Brandon,

36:04.622 --> 36:06.354
he's the one that made it happen.

36:06.983 --> 36:08.368
Thank you...

36:10.313 --> 36:11.585
so much.

36:11.705 --> 36:13.090
Yeah, you're welcome.

36:14.407 --> 36:16.524
Bye, Oli. See you later.

36:20.577 --> 36:23.634
The real goal when working
with kids with autism,

36:23.697 --> 36:25.197
is to connect with them,

36:25.260 --> 36:28.276
but to also help them
connect with their feelings.

36:28.352 --> 36:31.004
And that's what you did for Oli.

36:31.251 --> 36:33.194
You should feel really good about that.

36:34.191 --> 36:37.544
But you can't just bail every
single time you get embarrassed

36:37.553 --> 36:40.025
or have a bad session
with the patient, because

36:40.145 --> 36:43.954
there are plenty of
those days, too. Trust me.

36:45.343 --> 36:48.624
Oh, and you should also
watch where you're going.

36:51.334 --> 36:53.015
I just couldn't bring it up.

36:53.420 --> 36:55.721
You know, he's so
excited about getting out,

36:55.784 --> 36:57.415
and us getting a place together.

36:58.679 --> 37:00.719
Well, he wants to be a firefighter.

37:02.427 --> 37:04.414
Okay, but what do you want?

37:06.055 --> 37:07.637
I don't want to hurt Mike.

37:09.178 --> 37:12.280
But then I feel like it's worse
if I hurt my brother, you know.

37:12.680 --> 37:14.092
You think he'll understand?

37:14.568 --> 37:15.660
Mike?

37:16.393 --> 37:17.723
He'll understand.

37:18.295 --> 37:19.477
Excuse me.

37:20.434 --> 37:23.216
Are you the student responsible
for the art installation?

37:23.931 --> 37:25.194
Yes.

37:25.252 --> 37:26.897
I'm here with my son for the Open House.

37:26.915 --> 37:29.374
But I'm a professor at San
Diego School of Art and Design.

37:29.621 --> 37:31.882
Are you planning on going to art school?

37:32.759 --> 37:36.090
- Uh, I don't know.
- Well, if you are,

37:36.210 --> 37:38.422
I certainly hope you'll
consider applying with us.

37:38.462 --> 37:40.366
It's a really powerful piece.

37:46.075 --> 37:47.676
That's great.

37:47.862 --> 37:50.817
You're doing better than
me. Let's try again. Okay?

37:51.025 --> 37:52.199
Hey!

37:53.059 --> 37:54.699
Why aren't you at the Open House?

37:54.699 --> 37:57.845
I made an appearance,
just a very brief one.

37:58.160 --> 38:01.244
You know what, let's try
to change the key this time.

38:01.364 --> 38:03.065
G major.

38:03.655 --> 38:06.475
So it's still just all
white keys for this song.

38:06.475 --> 38:07.919
I'm done.

38:08.481 --> 38:10.312
Piano's too hard.

38:12.098 --> 38:14.216
Come on, everything's hard
when you're first learning it.

38:14.256 --> 38:17.957
- Yeah, that's not an excuse to give up.
- Why don't you two just get a room, huh?

38:18.281 --> 38:20.721
- What are you talking about?
- What? Did you think I'm stupid?

38:21.071 --> 38:22.276
You're screwing my brother.

38:22.289 --> 38:23.678
- No, she's not.
- That is not true.

38:23.691 --> 38:25.848
That's why you don't want sex with me.

38:25.871 --> 38:28.491
- Jesus!
- Of course, you want Brandon. I mean, he's smart.

38:28.611 --> 38:29.893
- Right?
- You gotta calm down

38:29.925 --> 38:31.606
or else you're gonna have a seizure.

38:31.726 --> 38:33.917
Hey, hey, hey! What is going on in here?

38:33.939 --> 38:35.849
- You and Mama know!
- What?

38:35.885 --> 38:38.075
You want Brandon to have her

38:38.097 --> 38:39.756
because you always want

38:39.769 --> 38:42.291
-  Brandon to have everything!
- Hey! Hey! Shh!

38:42.313 --> 38:44.663
Okay, enough. Brandon and
Mariana, upstairs, please now.

38:44.663 --> 38:45.634
Come on, let's go.

38:45.697 --> 38:47.252
Hey, look at me, look at me.

38:47.372 --> 38:49.791
Hey, Emma, sweetheart, I think
that Jesus needs a little rest.

38:49.805 --> 38:51.382
So why don't you head
home for a bit, okay, baby?

38:51.382 --> 38:52.573
Right, of course.

38:52.870 --> 38:56.277
Hey, calm down, okay. Calm down.

38:56.322 --> 38:58.786
Are you okay? Jesus?

38:59.312 --> 39:01.317
You okay? Jesus?

39:05.078 --> 39:07.586
Oh, my baby, talk to me.

39:08.917 --> 39:10.004
Oh, baby.

39:15.689 --> 39:17.428
- Is it true?
- No.

39:17.433 --> 39:19.499
I saw the way that you guys
were looking at each other.

39:19.517 --> 39:21.710
- Something's going on.
- There's nothing going on.

39:21.741 --> 39:22.935
I don't believe you.

39:22.970 --> 39:25.194
- Maybe Mom can get it out of you.
- Mariana, no,

39:25.212 --> 39:28.138
it's none of your business. For once
in your life, just stay out of it.

39:30.677 --> 39:33.611
Oh, my God. Emma's pregnant?

39:33.647 --> 39:36.145
She's pregnant, isn't she?
That's it. She's pregnant.

39:36.168 --> 39:38.550
Shh. No, she isn't pregnant.

39:42.121 --> 39:43.221
Anymore.

39:52.370 --> 39:53.961
You don't gotta hang around.

39:54.127 --> 39:55.700
I can watch her till they get home.

39:55.735 --> 39:57.157
That's sweet, but

39:57.350 --> 40:00.186
I don't want to miss a
moment with my grand baby.

40:00.200 --> 40:02.773
Oh, yeah, you must be sad
they're moving in with us.

40:02.808 --> 40:04.175
You're gonna miss 'em.

40:04.210 --> 40:06.891
So that's happening?
You're getting adopted?

40:07.175 --> 40:08.236
What do you mean?

40:08.721 --> 40:11.400
They wouldn't let her move in
here while Mike was fostering you.

40:12.021 --> 40:15.213
I know that she has a felony,
but she is not a bad influence.

40:16.116 --> 40:18.435
Well, now that he's adopting
you, that won't be an issue.

40:19.618 --> 40:22.058
Now we just have to get them married.

40:28.350 --> 40:30.579
_

40:30.589 --> 40:33.439
_

40:41.751 --> 40:44.447
- Hello!
- In here.

40:45.654 --> 40:47.560
We have an announcement.

40:48.050 --> 40:50.753
Miss Callie is being
scouted by an art school.

40:50.789 --> 40:52.455
She just asked me to apply.

40:53.416 --> 40:54.868
Hey, Robert.

40:54.926 --> 40:56.095
Hey.

40:56.931 --> 40:58.131
What's wrong?

41:02.665 --> 41:05.488
Troy Johnson won't take
the settlement deal.

41:05.991 --> 41:08.697
We tried everything we can. He
doesn't care about the money, so...

41:10.171 --> 41:11.506
we're going to trial.

